basic_info.summary:
Enthusiastic about communication with more than 6 years of experience in marketing agencies and departments.
|
After developing myself as a professional in communication projects, marketing, digital marketing, e-commerce, social networks, Amazon ... I decided to develop myself in the field of new technologies, learning how to program thanks to 4GeeksAcademy.
|
On a personal level, what fullfills me is learn languages, visit a museum, take a plane anywhere, enjoy a good movie or attend a concert. 
|
Curious, persevering and thoughtful, I always try to give my best in everything I do. My motto is to learn something new every day. Shall we speak?

education.details: Learning HTML, CSS, Bootstrap4, JS, Angular, React, SQL, Python during the intensive bootcamp.

International scholarship in the country with the best education of the world. Apart from learning about marketing in the Nordic countries, I had the opportunity to learn about different cultures and other ways of life.

experiences.details: As Communication Expert at American Express Global Business Travel, I develop my work in the field of external communication, by writting and translating press releases, communications to clients and content for the corporate website and social networks -as well as designing simple pieces for these communicationg in Photoshop; also, in the field of internal communication, with daily and monthly bulletins for employees, and other specific communications.

As Marketing Manager at Waterrevive and Motorrevive I am in charge of developing the Digital Marketing strategy including E-commerce, Communication, Social Networks, SEO and Blogs, Ads and recently, Amazon Seller.

basic_info.motto: When life hands you lemons, make lemonade.
basic_info.summary:
•	Experienced with analyzing, organizing and streamlining practices to help increase overall efficiency and productivity
•	Implements software and hardware, and performs basic IT troubleshooting
•	Proficient with various operating systems such as Windows and Mac OS as well as with software such as Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Skype and OneNote), Google Suite (Docs, Sheets and Slides) QuickBooks and Oracle  
•	Very computer savvy  
•	Types 60 WPM
•	Fluent in English and Spanish
•	Problem solver; highly organized and detail oriented

education.details: I studied business administration with concentration in marketing

experiences.details:
•	Established and reconfigured the company’s computer network by forming a centralized location with a server backup system and application software ensuring efficient communication flow, a company filing system, reservation database and proper use of bookkeeping software.
•	Oversaw company website design and functionality, established a merchant account for online customer payment options and implemented an online reservation request form; significantly increased operations, sales and cashflow.
•	Performed bookkeeping and managed company finances by monitoring accounts receivable and accounts payable transactions; oversaw a total budget of over $2million. 
•	Actively communicated and advised company owners on issues and offered solutions; served as a business consultant to assist with company growth and expansion.

•	Collaborated with company IT Department to streamline information flow and efficiently execute contracts using an e-signing software; reduced turnaround time by over 70%.
•	Prepared and reviewed over 25 Schedule of Values (SOV) packages for long term electrical contracting projects; responsible for communicating with Project Managers and Superintendents for payment to subcontractors in 2 of 3 regions.
•	Gathered and analyzed subcontractor payment reports for company CFO; provided feedback and identified existing issues.
•	Reviewed, approved, and processed over 70 bi-weekly invoices for payment

•	Assisted over 200 customers monthly; provided initial customer service, product check- in, and ran basic tests to determine product needs and service solutions. 
•	Performed computer related installations and upgrades; troubleshot operating systems and internet connection issues; installed computer related devices such as hardware, software, and peripherals; researched issues that were not common hardware and software problems.
•	Accurately handled and maintained sensitive customer information in accordance with store privacy policy.

basic_info.summary:
Debido a mi pasión por la programación me he formado de forma autodidacta en HTML5 y javascript. Actualmente me estoy formando como Full-Stack Developer y obtendré conocimientos avanzados en HTML5, CSS, Javascript, React, Python, SQL, Git, entre otras tecnologías. Mientras termino estos estudios, estoy en búsqueda de un trabajo que me permita, continuar mi desarrollo, practicar y crecer en el sector de la programación.
Soy una persona muy organizada, responsable, y perseverante, orientada al cumplimiento de horarios y plazos de entrega, además tengo una natural inclinación por facilitar un clima favorable de trabajo y trabajar en equipo.
Tengo muchas ganas de aprender, practicar y crecer como programador.

Debido a mi pasión por la programación me he formado de forma autodidacta en HTML5 y javascript. Actualmente me estoy formando como Full-Stack Developer y obtendré conocimientos avanzados en HTML5, CSS, Javascript, React, Python, SQL, Git, entre otras tecnologías. Mientras termino estos estudios, estoy en búsqueda de un trabajo que me permita, continuar mi desarrollo, practicar y crecer en el sector de la programación.
Soy una persona ambiciosa y responsable. En mis anteriores trabajos y experiencias de vida he aprendido a ser perseverante, innovador y a mantener siempre una alta motivación para mi trabajo. Aprendo rápido y sé trabajar en equipo o de forma independiente. Durante los últimos años también he desarrollado un gran interés en liderar grupos y me gusta mucho compartir conocimiento con la gente. 
Tengo muchas ganas de aprender, practicar y crecer como programador.

basic_info.summary:
I have a strong history in academia and aim to apply my research and analytical skills to different roles.
A hardworking self-starter, I approach my work utilizing a blend of research skills, creative flair, critical
thinking, and analytical abilities. Through the various projects I have completed during my 
academic career, I've cultivated verbal and written communication skills through presentations
and written publications, created sustainable relationships with informants, and managed various forms
of human feedback including audio recordings, video recordings, and surveys. I have also learned the value
of teamwork by collaborating with others in different states and countries to co-create publications and information
technology resources. My experiences have provided me with a strong sense of self-discipline and
motivation in organizing my own work schedule, excellent organizational skills, and meticulous attention to 
detail. I also have experience in digesting data with the goal of finding significant patterns in order to
improve efficiency and effectiveness.

basic_info.summary:
I am a creative and driven programmer with a background in music. 
I am looking to learn and grow in the coding profession and leverage my background as a professional musician to provide unique insight for clients and my team.
I enjoy working in teams and solving complex problems with elegant solutions.

education.degree: Master of Music in Studio Music and Jazz Trombone Performance
education.details:
Coursework included extensive study of contemporary and jazz styles, composition, musicology, recording techniques, pedagogy, and history. 
Performed across South Florida as part of the Concert Jazz Band and recorded mulitple professional albums. Worked with world famous professors including Dante Luciani, Brian Lynch, Dafnis Prieto, Martin Bejerano, and John Daversa.

education.degree: Bachelor of Music in Jazz Trombone Performance
education.details:
Coursework included study of jazz and classical music theory, ear training, piano, music history, music business, and improvisation.
Performed across North Texas in many Universtiy ensembles including lead trombone in the 3 O'Clock Lab Band. Studied under world-renowned faculty including Steve Wiest, Tony Baker, and Brad Leali.

experiences.details:
Recruit and manage musicians for major international cruise lines including Norwegian Cruise Lines, Carnival Cruise Lines, and Royal Caribbean Cruise Lines.
Auditioned musicians from all over the world and evaluated suitability for cruise work. Personally responsible for scheduling over 50 positions on cruise ships.
Worked closely with corporate teams from multiple cruise lines and built relations at universities and performing arts centers for recruitment.

Performed and toured full time as part of an 18 piece jazz orchestra across the United States, Canada, and Japan. Performed at many of the famous concert halls across the world including Cleveland's Severance Hall, the Adrienne Arsht Center for the Performing Arts in Miami, Orchard Hall in Osaka, Japan and Roy Thomson Hall in Toronto, Canada.
Also assisted in setup, tear down, and maintenance of stage equipment and directed stage hands on stage setup requirements.

basic_info.summary:

Actualmente me estoy formando como Full-Stack Developer y obtendré conocimientos avanzados en HTML5, CSS, Javascript, React, Python, SQL, Git, entre otras tecnologías. Mientras termino estos estudios, estoy en búsqueda de un trabajo que me permita, continuar mi desarrollo, practicar y crecer en el sector de la programación.
Soy una persona muy organizada, responsable, y perseverante, orientada al cumplimiento de horarios y plazos de entrega, además tengo una natural inclinación por facilitar un clima favorable de trabajo y trabajar en equipo.
Tengo muchas ganas de aprender, practicar y crecer como programador.

basic_info.focus: Learning tools to become a software developer in tech/fintech
basic_info.summary:
"My career until now has been choatic, fun and challenging. I have been able to learn from different companies how to become a
well rounded individual. My love of learning has pulled me into different directions now leading up to learning how to code, build websites and possibly change the world.
I have been able to adapt in very different positions, from managing a fast food resturant with over 75 employees, to handling over 100
catastrophe cases in different states and learning how to exercise empathy. Now I am learning how to write computer code and be able to build a dream to reality.
In the next 6 months I believe to acquire a junior developer position in a kick ass company.

education.details:
Learned the basics of coding with Html5 and Css.
Learned how to use coding social websites such as Github, Stack Overflow & Stack.
Built different projections as the lessons progressed with different programs.
Focus in Advertising & Marketing

experiences.details:
Fast paced energetic environment and results driven while providing
exceptional customer service. Daily review of property damage claims
information from the Independent Adjusters, complete the investigation
process and resolve the claim. Exercise strong organizational abilities and
empathetic interpersonal skills to assist the clients.
Investigate and adjust claims according to applicable laws and
policy provisions.
Build and maintain effective internal and external working
relationships. Collaborate with internal support teams and
management as appropriate.
Collabrated with Puerto Rico field office in handling over
16,000 Hurricane Maria Claims.

Performed a variety of tasks such as planning monthly goals,
hire and retain quality employees, inventory management,
scheduling employees while adhering to Florida
workplace guidelines, training employees and
shift managers in food safety, customer service
and daily maintance and cleanliness
Food Safety Certification
Outstanding Assistant Manager 2015

basic_info.summary:
Ingeniero Civil Industrial Mecánico de la Pontificia Universidad Católica de Chile,
Magíster en Ciencias de la Ingeniería, con experiencia en diversas áreas de negocios, 
principalmente en el ámbito de las inversiones y la planificación, evaluación e implementación 
de proyectos.

experiences.company: Inmob. e Inversiones Santa Isabel Ltda.
experiences.details:
Gestión activa patrimonio familiar.
  - Responsable de la toma de decisiones con relación a las nuevas inversiones, buscando
  siempre mantener un portafolio diversificado y ajustado a nuestro perfil riesgo/retorno.
  - Compra y venta de bienes raíces comerciales e industriales, gestionar y desarrollar nuevos
   proyectos comerciales, negociar y buscar la resolución de conflictos con distintas contrapartes.

experiences.role: Ingeniero de Planificación y Nuevos Negocios
experiences.details:
- Gestionar y decidir sobre las inversiones de la cartera líquida del grupo ascendente a
  $12.000 millones (en promedio).
- Evaluar proyectos de inversión relacionados a diversas industrias.
- Estudiar y recomendar sobre participar en distintos proyectos de capital de riesgo.
- Liderar el proceso de venta de una red de ductos soterrados para telecomunicaciones
  presentes en la V Región de por un monto cercano a USD 2 millones.
- Participar en la preparación de información estratégica relevante de la operación de la
  Compañía, tales como fusiones, compra/venta de empresas y nuevos negocios.
- Preparar informes de gestión de empresas de interés del Directorio.

- Modelación, evaluación y estructuración de nuevos proyectos. 
- Mayor logro, reestructurar y refinanciar deuda de Ruta de la Araucanía (MMUSD 380).
- Control, seguimiento y gestión de covenants financieros.
- Análisis de deuda, Bonos y Créditos Sindicados.
- Negociación con bancos, inversionistas, tenedores de bonos y otros.

basic_info.summary:
Ingeniero en informática con 3 años de experiencia dentro del rubro de las Telecomunicaciones. Iniciando en desarrollo web con perfilamiento al front-end sin dejar de lado el full-stack. Conocimiento en Python, ReactJs, JavaScript, GIT e implementación con Bootstrap.
Mi meta es continuar con el desarrollo de carrera en Proyectos full-stack como un aliado para la creación y mantenimiento de aplicaciones Web. Desarrollando estrategias para maximizar cada parte del proceso mediante esfuerzo y un optimo levantamiento de información y asesoramiento a clientes internos o externos.

education.details:
Utilización de aplicaciones y tecnología front como Html5, Css3, JavaScript y ReactJs.
Utilización de aplicaciones y tecnología back como Python, Flask, MYSql, sqLite.
Creación de Api-RESTfull.
Nociones de GIT para la administración de proyectos compartidos mediante repositorios remotos como locales.

experiences.role: Ingeniero Proyectos de Automatización de Procesos
experiences.details:
Levantamiento de información respecto de expectativas y alcance requerido para proyectos de automatización de procesos con principales involucrados.
Desarrollo back-end de solución digital que automatiza control de asistencia de colaboradores dentro de la empresa vía aplicacion web dentro de la nube de la empresa utilizando JavaScript (NodeJs, Jquery, Express) y nodeRed, generando reducción de tiempo de análisis para el departamento de R.R.H.H y optimizando la toma de decisiones respecto a remuneraciones, compensaciones, beneficios, vacaciones, entre otros.
Desarrollo de plataforma general para mejorar la experiencia de usuario de clientes internos que ordena y agiliza la utilización de las diversas app y soluciones creadas por el departamento utilizando Html5, Css y Bootstrap.

Gestión de relaciones de negocios con el cliente con el fin de llevar un control de hitos y avances de los proyectos a realizar.
Recopilación, validación y transformación de data de diversos orígenes para el mejoramiento de procesos de soporte y mantenimiento.
Encargado de administración de sistemas considerando el monitoreo de dominios Windows y Linux gestionando las actualizaciones y/o modificaciones de archivos necesarios para su correcto funcionamiento.
Desarrollo de aplicaciones orientadas a inteligencia de datos de comportamiento de consumidor de WebService (JAVA).
Encargado de brindar soporte al óptimo funcionamiento de aplicaciones y solucionar incidencias de segundo nivel (interrupción de servicios para clientes críticos) asignados a través de un software de gestión de tickets, asegurando cumplimiento de procesos, procedimientos y SLA's
Desarrollo de formularios, contenido y portadas para aplicación Web de la compañía (Wordpress y Prontus), gestión del contenido del sitio web. Encargado de soporte de sitio web.

basic_info.focus: Building a long-term career as a software developer.
basic_info.summary:
"Since graduating from college, I have focused my career on writing, editing, and creating
content for small businesses and entrepreneurs. I produce the written material that appears
on the websites of law firms, financial firms, and other small and medium businesses in
Florida and throughout the Southeast. Having worked with websites for a decade in a non-
technical position, I have grown to appreciate the role played by developers, as well as the
growth of the field. In 2018, I decided to shift my career focus to coding and software
development."

education.details:
Learned to create responsive websites using HTML, CSS, Javascript, 
Python, Django. Learned how to use coding social websites such as 
Github, Stack Overflow & Stack.

education.university: Sewanee — The University of the South
education.details: Member of the Order of Gownsmen academic honor society, Secretary of Beta Theta Pi fraternity, Habitat for Humanity volunteer.

work experience.details:
Produce and edit engaging and informative content for clients in several
industries, including banking/finance, real estate, technology, and 
health/fitness.
Clients include Investopedia, QuickBooks, GoDaddy, and Apartments.com.
Practice search engine optimization on all articles and blog posts, 
meeting keyword density requirements while maintaining flow and 
readability.
Maintain up-to-date knowledge of the Associated Press Stylebook and 
Chicago Manual of Style.

Contacted warm leads and responded to inbound inquries on LASIK eye surgery.
Spoke to an average of 150-200 prospects daily.
Never had a month of sales production ranked below third out of a team of over 40 sales reps.
Exceeded sales goals on a monthly basis.

I've been using HTML, CSS, Javascript, SQLite, Python and Ruby, starting to use React and Flask and looking forward to learn more frameworks.

basic_info.focus: Learning to become a Full Stack Developer and growing my network within Miami. Expaning my knowledge as much as possible to start my own company, and/or do consulting work for firms throughout the US.
basic_info.summary: I began an Accounting career while still in High School thanks to our "May Project" progam. This allowed all seniors to skip school for the month of May and get an internshhip instead. At the completion of my internship, I was offered a position as the Ar/Ap clerk. I contnued for 2 years while going to college, before moving into a Budget Analyst role for the NYS Department of Health. Following a brief stint there, for about a year, I was lucky enough to accept an offer as an Accoutning Manager for a privately owend company in NY. I completed my degree in Finance, while working as an Accounting Manager over the next 2+ years; and eventually saved enough money to quit and move to Miami. Upon arriving in Miami almost 2 years ago, I accepted another accounting Job for a public company. A year later, I decided I'd had enough of Accounting and took a job with Robert Half as the Client Service Director for the Southeast region. While working at Robert Half is when I decided to dive into coding/programming and really diversify my skillset.

education.details: I actually began at Siena as a Biology student determined to enter Med School and become an Anesthesiologist. However, I was forced to start working full time to support myself, and taking classes part time. Siena College is a small private school, so they weren't able to offer a part time Biology Degree. This forced me to switch my degree to either Finance or Accounting if I wanted to finish there. So I took Finance because it seemed more interesting at the time.

experiences.details: My primary repsonsibilities are to generate new business, and meet with the decision makers of companies to decide how best we can assist them in completing complex projects within Finance, Accounting, Audit and Tax.

I was an accountant overseeing the AR/AP departments, and also resonsibile for assiting with acquisitions and the transition of Financial data from the new company to ours. In addition, I was responsible for handling the banks, reconciliations, and payments both coming/going.

Handle all Accounting/Finance responsibilities including taxes for both locations (NY and NV). In addition, oversaw a team of 5 and reported directly to the President Owner. Handled all banking and AR/AP, collections/credit, and audit duties.

Soy una persona muy organizada, responsable, y perseverante, orientada al cumplimiento de horarios y plazos de entrega, además tengo una natural inclinación por facilitar un clima favorable de trabajo y trabajar en equipo.
Tengo muchas ganas de aprender, practicar y crecer como programador.

basic_info.focus: Learning to become a Full Stack Develope. Expaning my knowledge as much as possible to change my career and knowledge.
basic_info.summary: I began an Accounting career while still in High School thanks to our "May Project" progam. This allowed all seniors to skip school for the month of May and get an internshhip instead. At the completion of my internship, I was offered a position as the Ar/Ap clerk. I contnued for 2 years while going to college, before moving into a Budget Analyst role for the NYS Department of Health. Following a brief stint there, for about a year, I was lucky enough to accept an offer as an Accoutning Manager for a privately owend company in NY. I completed my degree in Finance, while working as an Accounting Manager over the next 2+ years; and eventually saved enough money to quit and move to Miami. Upon arriving in Miami almost 2 years ago, I accepted another accounting Job for a public company. A year later, I decided I'd had enough of Accounting and took a job with Robert Half as the Client Service Director for the Southeast region. While working at Robert Half is when I decided to dive into coding/programming and really diversify my skillset.

basic_info.focus: Becoming gainfully employed as a software developer
basic_info.summary:
"My career until now has been choatic, fun and challenging. I have been able to learn from different companies how to become a
well rounded individual. My love of learning has pulled me into different directions now leading up to learning how to code, build websites and possibly change the world.
I have been able to adapt in very different positions, from managing a fast food resturant with over 75 employees, to handling over 100 
catastrophe cases in different states and learning how to exercise empathy. Now I am learning how to write computer code and be able to build a dream to reality. 
In the next 6 months I believe to acquire a junior developer position in a kick ass company.

education.details:
Learned the basics of coding with Html5 and Css. 
Learned how to use coding social websites such as Github, Stack Overflow & Stack. 
Built different projections as the lessons progressed with different programs.

I learned how to build a business from scratch from making a business plan, to acquire funding, 
marketing, planning, human resource and finance.

experiences.details:
Fast paced energetic environment and results driven while providing 
exceptional customer service. Daily review of property damage claims 
information from the Independent Adjusters, complete the investigation 
process and resolve the claim. Exercise strong organizational abilities and 
empathetic interpersonal skills to assist the clients. 
Investigate and adjust claims according to applicable laws and
policy provisions.
Build and maintain effective internal and external working 
relationships. Collaborate with internal support teams and 
management as appropriate.
Collabrated with Puerto Rico field office in handling over 
16,000 Hurricane Maria Claims.

Performed a variety of tasks such as planning monthly goals, 
hire and retain quality employees, inventory management, 
scheduling employees while adhering to Florida 
workplace guidelines, training employees and 
shift managers in food safety, customer service 
and daily maintance and cleanliness
Food Safety Certification 
Outstanding Assistant Manager 2015

basic_info.summary: Aspiring junior web developer with a background in classical music and opera. In addition to my years of working as a professional musician with various organizations around the country, I have experience teaching both at the university level as an adjunct professor of lyric diction at Roosevelt University's Chicago College of the Performing Arts and as a private voice instructor for all skill levels. I enjoy working and collaborating as apart of a team and am very comfortable giving and leading presentations. Outside of my performing career, I run a small food blog sharing original recipes and cooking tips. I have experience writing posts, developing recipes, and providing high quality food photography for small and large brands and am familiar with a variety of digital marketing strategies including SEO and various social media platforms.

basic_info.summary:
Especialista en Sistemas con amplia experiencia en el área de Tecnología de Información (soporte, desarrollo e implementación de aplicaciones; coordinación de proyectos tecnológicos),
participación en proyectos de implementación de plataformas orientadas a servicios y a procesos (SOA/BPM). 
Conocimientos intermedios de la arquitectura de T24 (Temenos); IF Integration Framework; Temenos web Services; así como de las metodologías 
utilizadas para diseño de requerimientos de interfaces de conexión a T24, liderazgo  y conducción de equipos multidiciplinarios  para el cumplimiento 
de los objetivos de la organización.

I am passionate about new technologies and I am always willing to learn something new every single day.
Currently I am studying a Full Stack Web Developer bootcamp during which I am learning to improve my logical thinking and develop several programming projects.

education.details:
Full Stack Web Developer four intensive months bootcamp during which I am learning to improve my logical thinking and develop a wide range of programming projects with HTML5, CSS, Bootstrap,Java Script, React JS, Python, Flask, MySQL Alchemy and more.
  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point
During these six years I am able to learn a wide range of concepts to manage a company in the principles areas (Accountability, Sales, Marketing)

experiences.details:
My main responsabilities are to create marketing plans to our clientes for helping them to increase their sales.
  - Creating marketing plans to our clientes for helping them to increase their sales.
Develop marketing plans to our retails clients and our shoppers for increasing company´s sales.

-Analysis of market behaviour (volume, market shares, different segments) both own and competitors', and issuing conclusions that can be turned into opportunities for the company
-Analysis of different macroeconomic variables that may affect the market.
-Preparation of reports for the commercial network to follow up on the objectives set.
-Logistics distribution and stock control of the different materials to be implemented at the point of sale by the commercial network.
Follow-up and resolution of incidents in the reception by the commercial network of these elements.

basic_info.summary:
Psychologist from Universidad Católica de Chile, with 4 years of experience in HR consulting.
Nowadays studying Fullstack Developer at 4GeeksAcademy and finishing a Master 
in Quantitative and Qualitative Methods for Social Research. Skills include analytics with statistic 
software (SPSS) and Python, consultancy, organizational development, and lately a series of Front-end
technologies.

education.degree: Master at Quantitative and Qualitative Methods for Social Research

experiences.details:
eb | CONSULTING is a company that provides Human Resources services to other companies, 
which seeks to build organizational solutions based on expert processing of the best available evidence. 
In this company, I have worked both as a consultant on different HR issues (training, climate, 
organizational studies using statistics, between others), and also developing HR online platforms in the 
role of designing the wireframes, thinking the functionalities of the platform, and testing it (QA) before it goes to the final client. 
Thanks to my experience in this company I discovered that programming is my pasion, and I can't wait to look for new growing opportunities in this area.

Bci is a chilean bank which seeks to give quality financial services to its clients with security and closeness.
In this bank, I have worked as an Intership of the Human Resources Department, according to the University requirements to have my Psychologist title.
As part of my intership, I participated in the management of the first cycle of workshops 
for the Leadership Academy, and supported various recognition programs of the bank. I also participated 
in the development of a "Manager Kit" which consisted of a set of tools intended to support 
and recognize the newly managers of the bank.

basic_info.summary: I am a production engineer graduated from the Simon Bolivar University and with a postgraduate degree in marketing from the Central University of Venezuela, who has more than 14 years of experience working for transnational companies in the areas of Marketing and Sales, which is beginning to venture in the world of technology with the aim of making a living from coding

education.details:
Train experts with the necessary skills to
contribute ideas in the search for solutions to problems
management requirements, through the analysis and design
of marketing plans and programs in organizations
business.

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

The objective of the career is to train a highly qualified professional to perform in the production process, with adequate and balanced training for the design, improvement and installation of integrated systems of people, materials and equipment necessary in the industrial field and with knowledge of the economic factors, exchange of information and decision making to carry out this process in the best possible way. Production Engineering is the branch of engineering that deals with manufacturing processes and methods of manufacturing products and industrial goods. Pursues the integration of all relevant factors in order to have optimal solutions to complex problems related to the transformation of economic inputs into products necessary for society.

experiences.company: CICA LIFE Insurance Company of America
experiences.details: I expanded the CItizens client portfolio, generating my own client portfolio through a process of prospecting contacts, making calls to schedule appointments in which I conveyed to each prospect the importance of the product, achieving sales closings through the use of skills communicative, teamwork, and following up with each client, being tenacious in the sales process.

- Managing marketing strategies to uptake clients of mobile internet service, creating pricing strategies, developing
communicational strategies and promotional activities to the target market.
- Managing marketing strategies to uptake and retain B2B and B2C clients of public telecom service, developing communicational
strategies and promotional activities to the target market.
- Monitoring and evaluating monthly mobile internet and public telecom incomes and client quantity.

Selected Contributions:
- Increased mobile internet uptake ARPU from Bs. 236 on January 2014 to Bs. 405 on October 2014
- Achieved original 2014 uptake goal for mobile internet on July 2014
- Increased public telecom ARPU i n 25% since July 2014

- Developed and presented LG Mobile Product Road Map to carriers and distributors, using multimedia material and working with
advertising agency
- Monitored LG Mobile portfolio in carries and distributors, developing POP Material and giving training to sales representative in
order to increase it.
- Monitored competitors Product Road Map in terms of specifications, price and marketing and trade marketing activities.

Selected Contributions:
- Placed 7 most important LG products in all carriers nationwide since November 2010
- Increased rotation of LG Swift and LG Kellogg in Movistar Carrier in 12% since August 2011

- Developed and presented market and competition analysis to Alimentos Polar, PEPSICO and LG Mobile, through “The NielsenWay” Methodology
- Evaluated product launches’ impact and implementation of competitive distribution strategies, pricing and promotions
- Provided a complete view of current situation and opportunities in order to capitalize on the development of their strategic plans
  for management

Selected Contributions:
- Increased LG Mobile market share in 2 p.p. on December 2009
- Implementation of monthly findings format for PEPSICO INTERNACIONAL throughout the LATAM region. (Oct 2009)

education.degree: BACHELOR OF BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION IN BUSINESS MANAGEMENT

experiences.details:
Provide administrative and operational support for management team. Anticipate business needs and availability to develop work schedules. Authorize escalated customer issues using an internal support system.
- Analyze data to identify potential business opportunities and enhance workflow. - Increase satisfaction by resolving escalated customer service and support issues. - Collaborated with management to create a mentoring process to help team members improve their KPI’s. - Implemented trainings to standardize team’s knowledge and maintain KPIs. - Managed and distributed daily operations tasks amongst team while ensuring workload was leveled evenly and SLAs were met. - Managed queue levels during peak hours for Miami Greenlight Hub, partnering with on-shift agents to delegate incoming customers.

Managed a team, ensuring all daily tasks were met. Maximized productivity by promoting synergy and implementing policies to streamline workflow. Conducted market analysis to accurately plan inventory and estimate turnaround. Monitored all deliveries, providing assistance with transaction completion as needed.
- Boosted sales by cross-promoting products and services based on the buyer’s needs. - Maintained a strong working knowledge of inventory, insurance, and financing options. - Delivered high-quality results by focusing on management and team training.

basic_info.summary:
Yo he tenido experiencia en el sector de turismo y hoteleria, pero en el sector de tecnologia tengo poca experiencia pero la verdad 
la experiencia que he adquirido en 4Geeks es sumamente genial y he tenido un gran cambio del conocimiento que tenia y ha sido una gran
experiancia.

Dedicated to conquering the world through pragmatic programming and new order: 20 years of experience, in various IT worlds, walked by Technical Support, End User Support, Infrastructure Administrator, Monitoring Engineer, Project Director, 
Process Consultant, today Programmer tomorrow we will see.

experiences.details: Consulting, engineering and project management for the implementation of information technology management tools and processes.
Infrastructure, Systems and End User Support

projects.intro: Many of the projects carried out have had their greatest boom during my experience as Director of Monitoring Projects for different clients in Costa Rica and Central America. Provided a lot of collaboration in the implementation of IT Management Processes under international frameworks and standards such as ITL and COBIT

basic_info.focus: Learning tools to become a software developer in tech/fintech
basic_info.summary:
"My career until now has been choatic, fun and challenging. I have been able to learn from different companies how to become a
well rounded individual. My love of learning has pulled me into different directions now leading up to learning how to code, build websites and possibly change the world.
I have been able to adapt in very different positions, from managing a fast food resturant with over 75 employees, to handling over 100
catastrophe cases in different states and learning how to exercise empathy. Now I am learning how to write computer code and be able to build a dream to reality.
In the next 6 months I believe to acquire a junior developer position in a kick ass company.

education.details:
Learned the basics of coding with Html5 and Css.
Learned how to use coding social websites such as Github, Stack Overflow & Stack.
Built different projections as the lessons progressed with different programs.
Focus in Advertising & Marketing

experiences.details:
Fast paced energetic environment and results driven while providing
exceptional customer service. Daily review of property damage claims
information from the Independent Adjusters, complete the investigation
process and resolve the claim. Exercise strong organizational abilities and
empathetic interpersonal skills to assist the clients.
Investigate and adjust claims according to applicable laws and
policy provisions.
Build and maintain effective internal and external working
relationships. Collaborate with internal support teams and
management as appropriate.
Collabrated with Puerto Rico field office in handling over
16,000 Hurricane Maria Claims.

Performed a variety of tasks such as planning monthly goals,
hire and retain quality employees, inventory management,
scheduling employees while adhering to Florida
workplace guidelines, training employees and
shift managers in food safety, customer service
and daily maintance and cleanliness
Food Safety Certification
Outstanding Assistant Manager 2015

basic_info.focus: Becoming gainfully employed as a software developer
basic_info.summary:
"My career until now has been choatic, fun and challenging. I have been able to learn from different companies how to become a
well rounded individual. My love of learning has pulled me into different directions now leading up to learning how to code, build websites and possibly change the world.
I have been able to adapt in very different positions, from managing a fast food resturant with over 75 employees, to handling over 100 
catastrophe cases in different states and learning how to exercise empathy. Now I am learning how to write computer code and be able to build a dream to reality. 
In the next 6 months I believe to acquire a junior developer position in a kick ass company.

education.details:
Learned the basics of coding with Html5 and Css. 
Learned how to use coding social websites such as Github, Stack Overflow & Stack. 
Built different projections as the lessons progressed with different programs.

I learned how to build a business from scratch from making a business plan, to acquire funding, 
marketing, planning, human resource and finance.

experiences.details:
Fast paced energetic environment and results driven while providing 
exceptional customer service. Daily review of property damage claims 
information from the Independent Adjusters, complete the investigation 
process and resolve the claim. Exercise strong organizational abilities and 
empathetic interpersonal skills to assist the clients. 
Investigate and adjust claims according to applicable laws and
policy provisions.
Build and maintain effective internal and external working 
relationships. Collaborate with internal support teams and 
management as appropriate.
Collabrated with Puerto Rico field office in handling over 
16,000 Hurricane Maria Claims.

Performed a variety of tasks such as planning monthly goals, 
hire and retain quality employees, inventory management, 
scheduling employees while adhering to Florida 
workplace guidelines, training employees and 
shift managers in food safety, customer service 
and daily maintance and cleanliness
Food Safety Certification 
Outstanding Assistant Manager 2015

I just graduate from college with a bachelor in industrial designers.

I love creating new products also i really like the graphic design and the conceptualization

education.details:
is a process of design applied to products that are to be manufactured through techniques of mass production.

Its key characteristic is that design is separated from manufacture:

the creative act of determining and defining a product's form and features

takes place in advance of the physical act of making a product, which consists purely of repeated, often automated, replication.

This distinguishes industrial design from craft-based design,

where the form of the product is determined by the product's creator at the time of its creation
Generic college classes

basic_info.motto: Civil Engineer interested in the wolrd of Computer Science.
basic_info.summary:
Graduated in Civil Engineering from the Universidad de Costa Rica. 
Incorporated to the Federated College of Engineers and Architects of Costa Rica, credential N° IC-34897.

education.details: Specialty areas of choice; geotechnical, transportation, hydraulic and structures.

experiences.details: Writing reports, benchmarking and information analysis for the Integral Sustainable Urban Mobility Program of the Monterrey Metropolitan Area (PIMUS-ZMM, for its Spanish initials).
Review and grade assignments, short exams, and projects, as well as solving students’ doubts.

experiences.company: Laboratorio Nacional de Materiales y Modelos Estructurales (LanammeUCR)
experiences.details: Assistant in the Management and Evaluation of the National Road Network Unit, where my responsibilities included; analyzing and synthesizing data on surface irregularities (IRI), friction (GRIP), impact deflectometer (FWD) and pavement auscultation to determine the condition of Costa Rica's paved national road network, as part of the biennial evaluation report that is responsibility of LanammeUCR as the auditing body. In addition, I carried out visual auscultation work through the use of Geo3D software.

basic_info.summary:
I am someone who loves everything in the world of informatics and technology, specially in web developing.
Not only am I flexible when it comes to learning new things, but I am also excited to do so. I like to learn
things by myself or with a team, and I'm looking forward to learning the metholodologies of other people when
it comes to problem solving and any area.

education.details: Here I learned the basics of programming (C,C++ and Java), Databases and Object Oriented Programming, among other subjects.
Here I learned how to make web pages from the Front to the Back-end.

experiences.details: I managed the company's social media, mostly Linkedin, with tools like Sales Navigator.

basic_info.focus: Develop my programming skills and apply them on Data Science
basic_info.summary:
An analyst with 10+ years of experience in multinational companies in areas of Data analytics(Power Bi and Alteryx), customer service, fraud detection , Claims, Anti-Money Laundering (AML), and Anti bribery with knowledge in employee Engagement and Talent Development.
Focused in execution applying analytical skill to mitigate risk based on company guidelines, policies and procedures.

basic_info.summary:
I started working when I was young. I worked hard in construction, 
I knew the world of telecommunications installing lines for Telefonica, 
later I studied a CFGS in Telecommunications and Computer Systems, 
during two summers I alternated the work of lifeguard with the work at night during the weekends traveling all over Spain. 
I worked in a gymnasium and finally I entered the company where I have been working for 7 years 
and where I have gone through an electronic technical department, 
purchasing department and finally the department I work for today, 
information systems in which i am a DBA and maintain web applications.

education.details: First year in computer engineering.

education.degree: CFGS Telecommunications systems in computer science
education.details:
Higher level training in telecommunications and computer systems.

- Introduction to programming.
- Electronics.
- Hardware.
- Radio.
- Television.

experiences.details:
Developments, modifications and corrections in internal systems created in the company 
(inventory management, internal and external logistics, orders, productions, BoMs, layouts... ) 
and integrated with external applications (logistics operators, repairers, SAP...).
All these developments are made with Grails technologies (Groovy and Rails), GSP, JavaScript, .Net (VB.Net, C # and .NET Core).

  - Groovy and Rails
  - GSP
  - JavaScript
  - .Net

Analysis of client needs and elaboration of programmed tasks for software development.

  - Jira

Database administration in SQL Server and MySQL

  - Install, configure and manage databases.
  - Development team support.
  - Design data distribution and storage solutions.
  - Development of ad hoc stored procedures, both in SQL queries and server configuration.

basic_info.summary:
I am Oscar Mariño, I was born in May 85. I am a computer technician and I have worked in a few companies in which I have lasted the longest, it was one that has been an Avaya partner for 9 years, so I am qualified to support PBX Avaya both IP office and Comunication Manager, currently I work in a travel agency and my main function is the support of the teams so that the agents can carry out their work in the best possible way, in addition to offering support to our clients through a CRM tool

Soy Oscar Mariño naci en mayo del 85. y soy tecnico en informatica he trabajado en pocas empresas en la que mas he durado fue una que es partner de Avaya durante 9 años por lo que estoy calificado para dar soporte a PBX Avaya tanto IP office como Comunication Manager,  actualmente laboro en una agencia de viaje y mi funcion principal es el soporte de los equipos  para que los agentes puedan realizar su trabajo lo mejor posible, ademas de birndarle soporte a nuestros cliente a traves de una herraminta de CRM

education.details:
This course lasted approximately 16 weeks where I learned Front and End. We work with HTML 5 - CCS3 and Javascript and the DOM, in addition to Reac. In addition, I work with Git to be able to keep a history of the work in order to return in time if an error occurs or to be able to work in an orderly group and thus be able to merge what has been done. For the Back End, I work with Python and MySQL

Este curso tuvo una duracion de 16 semanas aproximadas donde aprendi Front y End. Trabajamos con HTML 5 - CCS3 y Javascript y el DOM, ademas de Reac. Ademas se trabajo con Git para poder llevar un historico del trabajo con la finalidad de volver en el tiempo si ocurre algun error o para poder trabajar en grupo de manera ordenada y asi poder fusionar lo realizado. Para el Back End se trabajo con Python y MySQL

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

It is basically a three-year career where I learned the basic notions of programming. I also worked with Pascal and Visual Basic.

Basicamente es una carrera de tres años donde aprendi las nociones basicas de programacion Ademas trabaje con Pascal y Visual Basic.

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

experiences.details:
In this company I have two roles. The main one is to give users on-site support. And that the systems remain active so that they can carry out their daily operations. And the second is to provide support in our systems to our clients. Detecting and giving you as much help as possible and escalate errors to the development department so they can be corrected

En esta empresa tengo dos roles. El principal es darle soporte en sitio a los usuarios. Y que los sistemas se mantengan activos para que puedar realizar sus operaciones diarias. Y el segundo es brindar soporte en nuestros sistemas a nuestros clientes. Detectando y brindalole la mayor ayuda posible y escalar los errores al departamento de desarrollo para que sean corregidos        

  - Bullet point

As you can see, I took a Full Stack Web Developer course, so now I am willing to develop pages as a freelance. With the idea of obtaining extra income besides continuing to develop and learn

From 2009 to 2019 I was working in an Avaya partner company where I developed and learned from the world of Avaya from design, through configuration and installation, to implementation and then support and troubleshooting customer failures and errors. at the level of Communication Manager and Ip Office

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

projects.intro:
Mientras trabaje en la empresa NGS Telecom Services realice varios proyectos de implementacion de PBX en todas sus fases. Desde el diseño de la pbx segun el requerimiento del cliente, pasando por el proceso de instalacion y configuracion hasta el proceso final de en entramiento y luego los procesos de troubleshooting para resolver los inconvenientes de los clientes
While working at the NGS Telecom Services company, carry out several PBX implementation projects in all its phases. From the design of the pbx according to the client's requirement, going through the installation and configuration process to the final process of entering and then the troubleshooting processes to solve the client's problems
Durante el curso de full stack realice varios ejercicios. aunque son sencillos solo es para mostrar y cumplir con una parte del curso de subir este perfil
During the full stack course, do several exercises. although they are simple, it is only to show and fulfill a part of the course to upload this profile

assignments.title: Final project
assignments.tagline:
Como proyecto final realice un pequeño sistema que me muestra los clientes previamente registrado por un personal de la empresa y luego y aun lado unas opciones para enviarle mensajes via telegram o por correo a dicho cliente. Dicho proyecto fue desarrollado en python y usando Mysql como base de dato
As a final project, I made a small system that shows me the clients previously registered by a company staff and then, and even some options, to send messages via telegram or by mail to said client. This project was developed in python and using Mysql as a data base

assignments.title: Avaya IP OFFICE
assignments.tagline:
Durante mi trayectoria en NGS pude realizar varias intalaciones, configuraciones y soporte con esta PBX. Entre mis conocimientos puedo mencionar, las actualizaciones configuracion de usuario, troncal IP y SIP, configuracion de usuario, grupos, audios, correo integrado y voice mail pro, aunque poco tambien he trabajado con el IPOCC una herramienta de administracion de call center
During my NGS career I was able to perform various installations, configurations and support with this PBX. Among my knowledge I can mention the updates user configuration, IP and SIP trunk, user configuration, groups, audios, integrated mail and voice mail pro, although I have also worked little with the IPOCC a call center administration tool

assignments.title: Avaya Communication Manager
assignments.tagline:
A igual que con el IP OFFICE, trabaje mucho con esta PBX desde la configuracion inicial hasta el soporte, donde de igual manera trabaje con la configuracion de usuarios, troncales, VDN, agentes. Tambien el uso del CMS, sistema de correo integrado y externo. He trabajado con versiones viejas hasta la mas nuevas en su version 7, desde el media gateway G700 y los G650. Avaya es un mundo tiene muchos equipos y he trabajado con mucho de ellos aunque aun faltan algunos por conocer he podido colaborar con los clientes que llegue a atender en la solucion de sus solicitudes.
As with the IP OFFICE, work a lot with this PBX from the initial configuration to the support, where in the same way it works with the configuration of users, trunks, VDNs, agents. Also the use of the CMS, integrated and external mail system. I have worked with old versions until the newer ones in version 7, from the media gateway G700 and G650. Avaya is a world with many teams and I have worked with many of them, although there are still some to know, I have been able to collaborate with the clients that I come to attend to in the solution of their requests.

basic_info.summary: I am a simple guy trying to get a bachelor's degree in electronic engineering.

Debido a mi pasión por la programación me he formado de forma autodidacta en HTML5 y CSS. Actualmente me estoy formando como Full-Stack Developer y obtendré conocimientos avanzados en HTML5, CSS, Javascript, React, Python, SQL, Git, entre otras tecnologías. basic_info.summary:
I'm currently an elementary school teacher. I have taught first grade for
five years and third grade for two years. I am interested in using my 
education expertise to develop educational websites and apps for students 
and teachers. I also have a background in professional development. I have 
trained faculty and staff how to effectively utlize technology in the 
classroom. I am very familiar with Microsoft Office 365 and Workplace by
Facebook. I have also held many leadership roles. In addtion to being the
technology liaison at my school site, I am the gradebook manager for the 
school site and the grade level chair for my third grade team.

education.details:
Attended education courses in teaching methodologies for elementary
school. Focusing on classroom assessment, literacy instruction,
classroom culture and politics in education. I also took courses in
exceptional student education. I have conducted research papers on 
effective strategies in literacy education. Worked closely with 
professors to create effective lesson plans and assessments. 

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

education.details:
Attended psychology courses for child development focusing on both early
childhood and school age children. I have conducted research papers that
focus on early child development. I have conducted research with my 
peers focusing on psychological issues that affects early child
development.

  - Bullet point
  - Bullet point

experiences.company: Miami Dade County Public Schools, Miami, Florida
experiences.details:
Elementary school teacher. Taught first grade for five years. Taught 
third grade for two years. Responsible for educating up to 30 students
using the Florida State curriculum and state standards. Responsible
creating effective lesson plans that target students needs. Served as 
grade level chair for two years where I was responsible for my first
grade team. I worked closely with administration to create school 
improvement plans. Served as the technology liaison. In this role I was 
responsible for keeping track of the most updated EdTech tools. Then I 
had to train my faculty in those EdTech tools. I was the recipient of
the 2018-2019 teacher of the year award.

  - Bullet point

and creation of newsletter workflow using Mailchimp.

In this role I managed the Training and Quality team within the Canon technical support team at Arvato Bertelsmann. 
My main tasks included

  - Liaising with client and different areas of the business to improve on quality and training processes

and as a liaison between ICT and the business to drive excellence to our websites.

I managed the publication process for all online content for Canon in the EMEA region,
including product launches and new product releases.

I created and published content for their web pages and worked on several web projects within eDreams.

basic_info.summary:
After graduating from the University of Florida, Sean began his career in digital advertising implementing online reputation management for at-risk clients. 
Soon transcending that role, Sean took on the role of Digital Manager for an advertising agency in North Miami where he strategized and executed campaigns across 
PPC, SEO, and social media mediums, utlimately reulting in the tripling of clients' media budgets due to positive ROI. 

Sean has now delved into programming in the hopes of procuring a technical position with more intellectual stimulation where he will be able to grow not just himself, 
but his company as well.

education.details:
Studied English from both an etymological and literay historical perspective. Graduated with 3.5 gpa.

  - Dean's List

experiences.details:
Managed entire client roster from  Fortune 500 companies to small (<$5M) and mid-sized businesses ($5M-$10M).
Strategized, negotiated and executed campaigns across traditional (radio and print) and digital (PPC, SEO, e-mail, etc.) 
mediums.

  - Worked with Carnival Cruise Line as the primary point of contact.
  - Managed agency's internal team to meet deadlines/deliverables and exceed expectations.

Created, executed, and managed all digital campaigns for entire client roster. Digital strategies consisted of
PPC, SEO, e-mail marketing and social media-driven foundations with constant optimization to acheive highest possible ROI while 
communicating brand's story. Wrote all consumer-facing copy for both digital ads as well as traditional
ads as featured by Aventura Magazine and News Aventura.

  - Tripled clients' media budgets with proven lead-generation.
  - Wrote copy for all clients in both digital and traditional mediums.

Personally created and executed SEO branding campaigns for 20-25 high networth accounts producing 150k + in client revenue.

  - Wordpress CMS
  - Produced additional $90k in referral revenue.

experiences.details:
Maintained and reconciled all general ledger accounts. Prepared and recorded monthly closing entries. Prepared and recorded journal entries by compiling, analyzing, and substantiating financial transactions as needed.
Prepared and recorded monthly intercompany elimination entries and adjustments for various bank subsidiaries. Performed ad hoc analysis as required by management. Assisted with compliance requirements including taxes and audits. 
Assisted wth analyzing financial statements on a monthly basis and reporting on variances.

experiences.details:
Performed comprehensive financial audits of public and privately-held entities across the banking, broker-dealer, not-for-profit, bio-medical, video production, and healthcare industries. 
Provided litigation support, due diligence support and forensic accounting for various high profile clients. Assisted in the compliance audit of a major regional Florida bank in relation 
to their adherence to the Bank Secrecy Act and its implementing regulations, the Anti Money Laundering rules.

experiences.details:
Parte del equipo de desarrollo a cargo del desarrollo Front end del sitio web de Sodimac.cl, Homy.cl y app. Revisión de mejoras para el sitio web,una de estas era mejorar el rendimiento del sitio web de Sodimac. Por lo que trabaje en la medición del tiempo de carga, ver posibles soluciones y cómo llevarlas a la práctica, coordinando soluciones con uno o más equipos. También, revisión de problemas relacionados al front end del sitio, detectando errores, ofreciendo soluciones y coordinando estas con las personas correspondientes.  
Toma de decisiones para el desarrollo y mejoras visuales. 
Conexión front end con base de datos, consumo de Api’s.
Apoyar la toma de decisiones técnicas para proyectos futuros y actuales
Desarrollo de proyectos para el área de Venta a Distancia.

Parte del equipo de desarrollo a cargo de LATAM Canales para el desarrollo de Allegro. A cargo de realizar Soporte para la base de datos de producción LATAM y solución de buck tracker Solucionando los errores e insertando datos. También formé  parte de Opera Hemiciclo. También orientado a los ejecutivos de CCO, esta es un sitio web con información relacionada a la operación, permite el ingreso de información relevante, o incluso realizar llamadas

Parte del equipo de supervisores a cargo de un grupo de personas estable de 15 personas, los cuales deben otorgar una atención de calidad y una solución efectiva a los clientes españoles del servicio telefónico y de adsl de Jazzplat España. En este sentido, dentro de las funciones estables que tiene un Tl está la capacitación constante de sus ejecutivos así también el crear reportes relacionados con la gestión y efectividad de su equipo

and sparked my passion for problem solving.

Debido a mi pasión por la programación me he formado de forma autodidacta en HTML5 y javascript. Actualmente me estoy formando como Full-Stack Developer y obtendré conocimientos avanzados en HTML5, CSS, Javascript, React, Python, SQL, Git, entre otras tecnologías. Mientras termino estos estudios, estoy en búsqueda de un trabajo que me permita, continuar mi desarrollo, practicar y crecer en el sector de la programación.
Soy una persona muy organizada, responsable, y perseverante, orientada al cumplimiento de horarios y plazos de entrega, además tengo una natural inclinación por facilitar un clima favorable de trabajo y trabajar en equipo.
Tengo muchas ganas de aprender, practicar y crecer como programador, sin olvidar que llevo unos 15 años desarrollando mi vida profesional como responsable de marketing a lo que mi nueva faceta como programador también me podría hacer alacanzar nuevas metas en este campo.

basic_info.summary:
I dedicated my life to coding since I was 13 years old, today I'm fortunate to make a living building and teaching code to everyone throughout my different business endeavors:

First I founded 4Geeks Developers Community: At the company, we built and launched 50 tech products during 10 years mainly focused in LatinAmerican markets. We opened offices in 7 different countries, 300 employees and more than $8,000,000 in revenues.

4Geeks Academy: Coding academy with 700+ alumni worldwide, ~90% of the graduates had an average 20% increase in salary after completing the program. $1,000,000+ in annual revenues in 6 locations.

BreatheCode: Not-for-profit open source community aiming to accelerate the way junior developers learn and evolve using technology.
